        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/edb3f5/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2017-12-18T15:42:37.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Tried these two Albarinos over the weekend:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<strong>field brook Albarino RustyGateFarmsVnyd/RRV (172 cs; 14.2%) SpotswoodeEstate/StHelena 2016</strong>: Med.gold color; very fragrant Albarino/melony/floral light perfumed talc/chalky rather spicy/cardamon slight waxy very attractive nose; rather tart/bit lean floral/melong/Albarino bit tangy/metallic slight perfumed talc/chalky bit saline/steely/savory structured flavor; very long very tart/lean/brisk strong floral/melony/Albarino rather savory/saline/steely bit spicy/cardamon light chalky/perfumed talc finsih; one of the most Galician-like Albarinos from Calif I can recall; a steal at $18.00 (PrimaIlC)</li>\n</ol>\n<hr>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li>\n<strong>Alberto Nanclares Albarino Dd\u2019O: RiasBaixas (13%; L-2016; <a href=\"http://www.JosePastorSelections.com\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">www.JosePastorSelections.com</a>; 30-60 yr old vines) 2016</strong>: Light yellow near colorless; somewhat earthy/chalky/mineral light floral/pear/Albarino slight bacony/smokey bit spicy/pimenton quite interesting/unusual nose; fairly tart/tangy/metallic floral/Albarino/mango/pear light smokey/spicy/pimenton/bacony some earthy/chalky fairly complex flavor; very long tart/tangy/metallic/steely fairly floral/pear/mango/Albarino/carnations light bacony/pimenton/smokey bit earthy/chalky complex finish; an unusual bit exotic complex rendition of Galician Albarino. $28.00 (AV)</li>\n</ol>\n<hr>\n<p>A wee BloodyPulpit:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>field book: This was a wine that showed up last week in my Prima IlConsorzio shipment. A label I\u2019d never heard of before. Apparently used for wines made from purchased grapes. They also make a Syrah from Griggin\u2019sLair vnyd. Normal retail on this Albarino is $32, so the IlConsorzio price is very good.<br>\nBack in the days (by cracky) when I used to follow NapaVlly Cabs, Spotswoode was one of my favorites. But, as the price escalated, I dropped out of following it.<br>\nI seem to recall that Spotswoode was recently sold, but I can\u2019t track down that story.<br>\nTom</li>\n</ol>",
