my Prima IlConsorzio shipment. A label I\u2019d never heard of before. Apparently used for wines made from purchased grapes. They also make a Syrah from Griggin\u2019sLair vnyd. Normal retail on this Albarino is $32, so the IlConsorzio price is very good.<br>\nBack in the days (by cracky) when I used to follow NapaVlly Cabs, Spotswoode was one of my favorites. But, as the price escalated, I dropped out of following it.<br>\nI seem to recall that Spotswoode was recently sold, but I can\u2019t track down that story.<br>\nTom</li>\n</ol>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Love the Spottswoode Albari\u00f1o, and no, the estate hasn\u2019t been sold.</p>",
